ollar by purchasing additional gift cards and certificates at their business.','https://s.yimg.com/cv/apiv2/social/images/yahoo_default_logo-1200x1200.png','2022-12-02 00:50:00.0','Dec. 1—DICKINSON — Stark Development Corporation is rewarding shoppers for going local. Over the next few weeks they can enter their receipts from Stark County businesses to win weekly prizes for…','https://news.yahoo.com/stark-development-rewards-consumers-005000411.html',0,1,'2022-12-02 05:00:31','2022-12-02 05:00:31'),(183,'Council Post: Growing Your Business Without Growing It To Death','Scott Ford','President of California Builder Services, a real estate consulting firm specializing in DRE Reports, HOA Budgets and Reserve Studies.\ngetty Why do at least 50% of businesses fail within the first five years? Why do companies that make millions go out of business? Business owners seem to face insurmountable odds against their success. These individuals put everything on the line—their health, marriages and families—while the majority continue to fail year after year. Although social, political and economic conditions change, I think there is another factor involved: the pressure to keep growing.','https://imageio.forbes.com/specials-images/imageserve/6387808d2e8bd16b8ec8a8bc/0x0.jpg?format=jpg&width=1200','2022-12-01 15:15:00.0','Pushing your business past its capabilities can cause the company to fail. So how can you know the right time to stay steady or to push for more growth?','https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbesbusinesscouncil/2022/12/01/growing-your-business-without-growing-it-to-death/',0,1,'2022-12-02 05:00:31','2022-12-02 05:00:31'),(184,'15 businesses named as finalists for 2022 MARKETPLACE awards','Ein News','Winners will be announced at Dec. 6 conference\n\nMADISON, WI. DEC. 1, 2022 – Fifteen Wisconsin companies and individuals have been named as finalists for the 2022 MARKETPLACE Governor\'s Awards, which honors Wisconsin businesses owned by minorities, women and service-disa